5|$|From the 1980s to the present, Apple {{has been}} <b>plaintiff</b> or {{defendant}} in civil {{actions in the}} United States and other countries. Some of these actions have determined significant case law for the information technology industry and many have {{captured the attention of}} the public and media. Apple's litigation generally involves intellectual property disputes, but the company has also been a party in lawsuits that include antitrust claims, consumer actions, commercial unfair trade practice suits, defamation claims, and corporate espionage, among other matters.|$|E
